A chairde,

T=E1 s=FAil agam go bhfuil sibh go maith!

Our 'Seanfhocal' for this week was: 'Is fearr an tsl=E1inte na an t=E1inte'=
-
"Health is better than wealth," emphasizing that good health is more valuab=
le than riches. "T=E1inte" - old Irish word for cattle/a herd (what wealth =
used to be measured in!), and "sl=E1inte" means health. It's a reminder tha=
t wealth is meaningless if you don't have your health!

Last night:

  *
We covered the PowerPoint 'Na Braithra' (attached) in full. We looked at th=
e 3 categories or groups of Irish Verbs 'An Ch=E9ad R=E9imni=FA', 'An Dara =
R=E9imni=FA' agus 'Na Briathra Neamhrialta' as well as the leathan le leath=
an, caol le caol rule.
